However, port 30005 is also notably linked to various forms of malware. Trojan-Dropper.Win32.Delf.xk is known to utilize this port (along with 30006 and 30007) for its operations. Additionally, other Trojans, such as "Backdoor JZ" and "Litmus," have been observed using port 30005. Therefore, if this port is found open on a personal computer, it could indicate a potential malware infection."""
